The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) has arraigned a dismissed judge of the Federal High Court, Justice Rita Ofili-Ajumogobia, at a Federal High Court in Lagos on the alleged fresh fraud charge. She was docked today before Justice Mohammed Aikawa on an 18-count charge bordering on corruption and unlawful enrichment by a public officer. The defendant, however, pleaded not guilty to 17 of the 18 counts in which her name was mentioned. The anti-graft agency could not produce her co-accused, Mr Godwin Obla, a Senior Advocate of Nigeria (SAN), who was named in one of the counts. The silk was said to have been at large. Arguments are on-going on the defendant’s oral bail application. Details later The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) has filed fresh corruption charge against a dismissed judge of the Federal High Court, Justice Rita Ofili-Ajumogobia and a Senior Advocate of Nigeria (SAN), Mr. Godwin Obla, at the Federal High Court in Lagos. The fresh charge was filed barely 24 hours… In “News” The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) has filed fresh corruption charge against a dismissed judge of the Federal High Court, Justice Rita Ofili-Ajumogobia and a Senior Advocate of Nigeria (SAN), Mr. Godwin Obla, at the Federal High Court in Lagos. The fresh charge was filed barely 24 hours after… In “News” Barely 20 minutes after a case of unlawful enrichment initiated against her by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) was struck out by a Lagos High Court, Ikeja, a dismissed Judge of the Federal High Court, Justice Rita Ofili-Ajumogobia yesterday again became a guest of the anti-graft agency.… In “News”